---
const pillars = [
	{
		title: "The Stream",
		subtitle: "Liveness without interruption",
		items: [
			"Happen event log rendered as a contextual timeline.",
			"Shows who spawned what, which liners intercepted it, and latency.",
			"No prompts to babysit—just observability.",
		],
	},
	{
		title: "The Inbox",
		subtitle: "Async review surface",
		items: [
			"Shadow Mode diffs, policy holds, clarifications.",
			"Each item opens into contextual thread + artifact.",
			"Approve, discard, or leave guidance without pausing the swarm.",
		],
	},
	{
		title: "Notifications",
		subtitle: "Three-tier urgency",
		items: [
			"Low: badge updates and digest emails.",
			"High: OS notifications when liners block execution.",
			"Critical: crash popovers that freeze the mission until triaged.",
		],
	},
];
---

<section
	id="async"
	class="border-b border-[hsl(var(--border))]/70 bg-[hsl(var(--background))]"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div
			class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr,0.9fr] lg:items-center lg:gap-16"
		>
			<div class="space-y-5">
				<p
					class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]"
				>
					Human-in-the-loop · Reimagined
				</p>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
					Async collaboration beats chat fatigue.
				</h2>
				<p
					class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]"
				>
					Chat-based AI locks humans into waiting for typing
					indicators. Guru shifts the power dynamic: you dispatch work
					through a fast command surface and review the results when
					you are ready. Think Linear issues meets GitHub review
					threads—only every artifact is generated by agentic swarms
					instead of junior engineers.
				</p>
				<div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
					<div
						class="rounded-2xl border border-[hsl(var(--border))] bg-[hsl(var(--card))] p-4 text-[13px]"
					>
						<h3
							class="text-sm font-semibold text-[hsl(var(--foreground))]"
						>
							Manager mode
						</h3>
						<p class="text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]">
							Run five missions in parallel. Guru routes updates
							into contextual, comment-style threads, so you
							review swarms the way you review pull requests.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div
						class="rounded-2xl border border-[hsl(var(--border))] bg-[hsl(var(--card))] p-4 text-[13px]"
					>
						<h3
							class="text-sm font-semibold text-[hsl(var(--foreground))]"
						>
							Worker mode (optional)
						</h3>
						<p class="text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]">
							Need to pair with an agent? Open the real-time
							stream and drop into a contextual thread. It’s sync
							when you want it, async when you need focus.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div
				class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-[hsl(var(--border))] bg-[hsl(var(--card))]/95 p-4 shadow-xl lg:p-6"
			>
				<div
					class="mb-2 text-[11px] font-medium text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]"
				>
					Mission Control stack
				</div>
				<div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
					{
						pillars.map((pillar) => (
							<div class="rounded-2xl border border-[hsl(var(--border))]/80 bg-[hsl(var(--background))] p-4 text-[11px]">
								<div class="mb-2">
									<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[hsl(var(--foreground))]">
										{pillar.title}
									</p>
									<p class="text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]">
										{pillar.subtitle}
									</p>
								</div>
								<ul class="space-y-1.5 text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]">
									{pillar.items.map((item) => (
										<li class="flex gap-2">
											<span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[hsl(var(--primary))]" />
											<span>{item}</span>
										</li>
									))}
								</ul>
							</div>
						))
					}
				</div>
				<div
					class="rounded-2xl border border-dashed border-[hsl(var(--border))] bg-[hsl(var(--background))] p-4 text-[11px] text-[hsl(var(--muted-foreground))]"
				>
					<p
						class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-[hsl(var(--foreground))]"
					>
						How operators reconcile the shift
					</p>
					<p>
						Frame Guru as “Manager Mode.” Agents are the workers;
						humans orchestrate outcomes. The UI looks and feels
						approachable, so leaders immediately understand how to
						triage, comment, and approve without falling back to
						prompt-response loops.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
